page.title: 10Architecture.
page.content: In the village of Leintwardine, { {Watling Street}has many old houses but a few have had their stone work or old brick plastered or pebble dashed over. There are a lot of timber framed houses. At the bottom of Watling Street there are a few houses with bow windows. Every house has a porch. A lot of houses are stone with brick edges and brick rims around the window.{Rosemary Street.}Rosemary is a modern estate, which has a fire station built with corrugated iron and modern brick. In Rosemary there are two different coloured bricks, light coloured and red brick.{ } Along{High Street}there are again a lot of coloured pebble dashed houses. There are also a few houses with sash windows. At the end of High street there are a few thatched cottages and a lot of stone buildings.
